Usage: moveGroupPins [-help] [-depth <float>] [-end_location {x y}]
                     [-expand_spacing_factor <float>] [-layer <string>]
                     -loc {x y} [-moveOnLayer <string>] [-noFixed]
                     [-spacing <float>] [-spread_type <string>]
                     [-start_location {x y}] [-width <float>] [-withOverlap]

-help                              # Prints out the command usage
-depth <float>                     # depth of the pin or pin group, in
                                   # micrometers (float, optional)
-end_location {x y}                # specifies the coordinates where pins
                                   # should end when pin spreading along a
                                   # range (point, optional)
-expand_spacing_factor <float>     # speify value will be multiplied to the
                                   # current spacing in tracks (float, optional)
-layer <string>                    # name of the metal layer for the pin or pin
                                   # group (string, optional)
-loc {x y}                         # new x and y location for the pin or pin
                                   # group (point, required)
-moveOnLayer <string>              # specify move on layer UP or DOWN
                                   # (string, optional)
-noFixed                           # moved pins or group of pins are not set to
                                   # the fixed status (bool, optional)
-spacing <float>                   # display the spacing bwteen pins for
                                   # multi-pin editing (float, optional)
-spread_type <string>              # specify how to mange spacing between pins
                                   # while moving grouped-pins (string, optional)
-start_location {x y}              # specifies the coordinates where pins
                                   # should start when pin spreading along a
                                   # range (point, optional)
-width <float>                     # width of the pin or pin group, in
                                   # micrometers (float, optional)
-withOverlap                       # The moved pins maybe overlap
                                   # (bool, optional)